******
[2] Uganda
Date: Sat 12 May 2018
Source: Outbreak News Today [edited]
http://outbreaknewstoday.com/uganda-cholera-outbreak-in-kampala-measles-outbreak-declared-in-26-districts-26473/


The Ministry of Health has announced an outbreak of measles in 26 districts across the country, according to a Monitor-Uganda report. Health minister Jane Aceng named the most affected districts as Amuru in northern Uganda, and Kamuli, Mbale, and Butebo in the east of the country.

Dr. Aceng, while addressing Alebtong District leaders at the council hall on [Wed 9 May 2018], said: "We already have 26 districts with measles outbreak, so DHO [district health officers] need to wake up and intensify routine vaccination for measles. The most affected group is children under 5 years."

She said the government, in collaboration with development partners, would carry out mass immunization against the disease of all children under 5 years.

