[3] England
Date: Fri 11 May 2018, 8:53 PM
Source: The Sun [edited]
https://www.thesun.co.uk/news/6268027/measles-outbreak-england-europe-mmr/


England has been hit by a sharp rise in measles cases. More than 400 cases [between 1 Jan and 9 May 2018] have been identified, linked to large outbreaks in Europe, according to Public Health England.

Dr. Mary Ramsay says the cases are seen mostly in teens and young adults who missed their MMR [measles, mumps, rubella vaccine].

The figure is already higher than 2017, when there were 267 confirmed cases. In 2016, there were 531 confirmed cases.

There are large outbreaks in Romania and Italy and people travelling to these countries should check health advice.

[Byline: Shaun Wooller]

