[5] USA: New York, New Jersey, Connecticut: alert
Date: Sat 12 May 2018, 9:36 AM
Source: Patch [edited]
https://patch.com/new-york/southeast/putnam-measles-outbreak-spreads


A total of 3 more measles cases have been reported as part of the outbreak in Putnam County. Nearby, the Orange County Health Department issued a warning Fri [11 May] about potential measles exposure at a medical facility in Monroe [New York]. Moreover, the New Jersey Health Department issued a warning for people who traveled through Newark Airport [New Jersey].

The Putnam outbreak now involves 6 people from 3 states and overseas. First announced [4 May 2018], it was started by an international traveler to the county.

Putnam health officials said 2 of the new cases are California residents and 1 is a Putnam resident. The initial victims were 2 local residents and a Connecticut resident.

The Putnam outbreak started with an international family from France who was visiting at the Watchtower headquarters in Patterson. So far 90 people have been interviewed because they may have been exposed.

The Orange County Department of Health is advising residents of a potential measles exposure on [29 Apr 2018] at a Monroe medical facility as a result of an infected traveler.

[Byline: Lanning Taliaferro]

